        <definition>void Game::Initialize</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>Initialize</name>
        <qualifiedname>Game::Initialize</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initialize the game engine and all subsystems. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Performs the following initialization steps:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Initializes SDL and its extensions (SDL_image, SDL_ttf, SDL_mixer)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Creates the game window</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Creates the hardware-accelerated renderer</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Initializes ImGui for debug UI</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Loads initial game assets</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Sets up the initial game state</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>void (Consider changing to bool for error handling)</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Must be called before <ref refid="classGame_1a96341ca5b54d90adc3ecb3bf0bcd2312" kindref="member">Run()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="warning"><para>Calling this multiple times without calling <ref refid="classGame_1a0311a22e53ddb906aa1024efdced0e2f" kindref="member">Destroy()</ref> first may cause resource leaks</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classGame_1a0311a22e53ddb906aa1024efdced0e2f" kindref="member">Destroy()</ref></para>
</simplesect>
<xrefsect id="todo_1_todo000001"><xreftitle>Todo</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para>Change return type to bool to indicate success/failure </para>
<para>Add error logging for initialization failures </para>
</xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>
        </detaileddescription>
