      <memberdef kind="function" id="classGame_1a96341ca5b54d90adc3ecb3bf0bcd2312" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void Game::Run</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>Run</name>
        <qualifiedname>Game::Run</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Execute the main game loop. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Runs the game loop until the user quits. Each iteration of the loop:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Calculates delta time since last frame</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Processes input events via <ref refid="classGame_1a770db4782ba58f6e8ae098fccf8ba571" kindref="member">ProcessInput()</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Updates game state via <ref refid="classGame_1a1c5373c68261c54aff03e6abe40fee52" kindref="member">Update()</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Renders the frame via <ref refid="classGame_1a0897730fc9fed789f6c0f11d21a0c14a" kindref="member">Render()</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Limits frame rate to target FPS</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para>The loop continues until a quit event is received (e.g., window close, ESC key, or programmatic quit request).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This is a blocking call that returns only when the game exits </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Frame rate is typically capped at 60 FPS</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classGame_1a770db4782ba58f6e8ae098fccf8ba571" kindref="member">ProcessInput()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classGame_1a1c5373c68261c54aff03e6abe40fee52" kindref="member">Update()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classGame_1a0897730fc9fed789f6c0f11d21a0c14a" kindref="member">Render()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
