      <memberdef kind="function" id="classGame_1a770db4782ba58f6e8ae098fccf8ba571" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void Game::ProcessInput</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>ProcessInput</name>
        <qualifiedname>Game::ProcessInput</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Process all input events from the user. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Polls and handles SDL events including:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Keyboard input (key press/release)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Mouse input (button press/release, motion, wheel)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Window events (close, resize, focus)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="classGame" kindref="compound">Game</ref> controller input</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>This method is called once per frame by <ref refid="classGame_1a96341ca5b54d90adc3ecb3bf0bcd2312" kindref="member">Run()</ref> and updates the internal input state that can be queried during <ref refid="classGame_1a1c5373c68261c54aff03e6abe40fee52" kindref="member">Update()</ref>.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>ImGui events are processed first to allow UI interaction </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Input state is accumulated and can be queried in <ref refid="classGame_1a1c5373c68261c54aff03e6abe40fee52" kindref="member">Update()</ref></para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classGame_1a96341ca5b54d90adc3ecb3bf0bcd2312" kindref="member">Run()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classGame_1a1c5373c68261c54aff03e6abe40fee52" kindref="member">Update()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
