      <memberdef kind="function" id="classGame_1a0897730fc9fed789f6c0f11d21a0c14a" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void Game::Render</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>Render</name>
        <qualifiedname>Game::Render</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Render the current game state to the screen. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Performs the following rendering steps:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Clears the screen with background color</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Renders game background</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Renders all game entities (sprites, text, shapes)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Renders UI elements</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Renders debug information (ImGui)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Presents the final frame to the screen</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para>Rendering order is important for proper layering (back to front).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Called once per frame by <ref refid="classGame_1a96341ca5b54d90adc3ecb3bf0bcd2312" kindref="member">Run()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Uses double buffering - changes are not visible until SDL_RenderPresent()</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classGame_1a96341ca5b54d90adc3ecb3bf0bcd2312" kindref="member">Run()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classGame_1a1c5373c68261c54aff03e6abe40fee52" kindref="member">Update()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
